### Check if Payload field is an array type using fieldIsArrayType

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/tools/claude-plugin/skills/payload/reference/FIELD-TYPE-GUARDS.md

Utilizes the `fieldIsArrayType` guard to determine if a Payload field is of type 'array'. This allows safe access to array-specific properties like `minRows` and `maxRows`, which are relevant for configuring array field behavior.

```typescript
import { fieldIsArrayType } from 'payload'

if (fieldIsArrayType(field)) {
  // field.type === 'array'
  console.log(`Min rows: ${field.minRows}`)
  console.log(`Max rows: ${field.maxRows}`)
}
```

