### Check if Payload field has sub-fields using fieldHasSubFields

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/tools/claude-plugin/skills/payload/reference/FIELD-TYPE-GUARDS.md

Uses the `fieldHasSubFields` guard to recursively traverse an array of Payload fields. This guard ensures that `field.fields` can be safely accessed for types like group, array, row, or collapsible fields. It's essential for navigating nested field structures.

```typescript
import type { Field } from 'payload'
import { fieldHasSubFields } from 'payload'

function traverseFields(fields: Field[]): void {
  fields.forEach((field) => {
    if (fieldHasSubFields(field)) {
      // Safe to access field.fields
      traverseFields(field.fields)
    }
  })
}
```

```typescript
if (fieldHasSubFields(field) && !fieldIsArrayType(field)) {
  // Groups, rows, collapsibles only (not arrays)
}
```

